cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of training deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification with mislabeled training samples, which is a common issue in real image data sets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an auxiliary image regularization technique that optimizes the stochastic Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM) algorithm, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms used in machine learning, i.e., cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of mutual context information among training images, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence, i.e., cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a subfield of multimedia, i.e., cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a regularized CNN model that is resistant to label noise in training data, which falls under the category of neural network regularization techniques, i.e., cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
